8. Pod vs. Deployment
Aspect	Pod	Deployment
Definition	Smallest unit, runs containers	Higher-level controller managing Pods
Scaling	Not scalable directly	Supports scaling and rolling updates
Use case	Single instance	Production workloads needing resilience


🎯 Interview Tip
When asked about Pods, don’t just define them — emphasize why Kubernetes uses Pods instead of just containers:

They provide a higher-level abstraction.

Enable grouping of tightly coupled containers.

Simplify networking and storage management.

